  libsodium is consumed as a system shared library (the Fedora 43 distro
  package `libsodium-1.0.22-1.fc43`) via a thin Interfaces.C binding
  (`Entity_Core.Crypto`); it is dynamically linked (`-lsodium`), not vendored
  or statically bundled. Its source and full license text are available at
  https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium.

CBOR (ECF canonical codec), Base58, the multicodec LEB128 varint, and the
test/conformance runner are hand-rolled in-repo (no third-party code, no
Alire crate dependencies) — see README.md and arch/PROFILE-RATIONALE.md.
